      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-01-18</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-01-21T16:15:18Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Consumer Telephone Records Protection Act of 2006 - Amends the federal criminal code to prohibit: (1) the obtaining by fraud or other unauthorized means of confidential phone records information from a telecommunications carrier or IP-enabled voice service provider (covered entity); and (2) the sale of such records by any person, including any employee of a covered entity. Exempts law enforcement agencies.</p> <p> Imposes a fine and/or imprisonment for up to five years. Doubles such penalties for violations occurring in a 12-month period involving more than $100,000 or more than 50 customers of a covered entity. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
